Baumgarten reads הובא. At the paleographical level this needs careful analysis. Sign_11 was interpreted to be the lower right merger of the vertical stroke and lower foot. Does this concord with other bets in the scribal hand? RECHECK. If sign_11 is a bet, then perhaps sign_13 is the left most edge of the lower foot of a bet. The aleph then would have been small and was a ligature with the bottom foot—however, this requires evidence. We know he does this waw/yod and beth, but with aleph? RECHECK.
